Title: Bergen Norway Walking Tour - The Capital of the Fjords | 4K HDR
Description:
Join us and enjoy this evening walk in the second-largest city in Norway, Bergen. We start our walk near a small lake with a fountain in the heart of Bergen bordered by a beautifully maintained park with scenic views of nearby mountains. We discover a picturesque pavilion with interesting architecture surrounded by colourful flowers.

The historical buildings, such as The National Stage which is the home of modern, classical drama, and musicals, and many stunning sculptures and monuments describe the beauty and might of Bergen Norway.

We continue our walk towards Bergen Harbour where we can see a medieval wharf with its colourful iconic colourful, wooden-clad boat houses, the Bryggen, which has been listed by UNESCO as a World Heritage Site. 

Finally, we explore a small restaurant where we can try reindeer sausages üå≠üå≠üå≠!

Title: Surprising My Cameraman With A ¬£110K Daily!
Description:
Change your car with Carwow: https://bit.ly/Change-Your-Car-2609 

You'll often see Mat driving any number of luxurious and high-end cars on this channel, but have you ever asked yourself - what do the Carwow camera crew drive? 

Well wonder no more! This is the Carwow Van Haven van, and if anything, we think it might be better and more luxurious than some of the cars we show off on this channel! So let's take a closer look at it...

The van started life as a VW Transporter. However, the Van Haven team have gone to town on it, ripping out almost all elements of the interior and allowing the Carwow crew to spec it as they wished. As a result, the cabin is now fitted with super-comfortable brown leather seats in the front and rear, and there's even a set of retractable tables in the rear to help with working on the go! 

But that's not all! The van is chocked full of power points, which allows the team to have a coffee machine on the go at any hour of day on a shoot, and there's even a built in fridge! There's an awning on the side that also let's the team find shelter from the elements when we're on the drag strip. 

So the van is an absolute treat, but as you can imagine, it's not exactly cheap! Want to find out how much it costs? Stick with Mat for this all-new review to see for yourself!

Description: 

In this video we'll have a look on some unique towns in the united states of America. What makes them so unique is the fact that because the border between USA and Canada is the 49th parallel, these United States towns remained cut off from mainland US and surrounded by Canada.
I'm talking here about Angle Inlet and Point Roberts and their story is truly awesome.
In this video we'll come back to Europe and talk about a very special border located right
But we'll talk more about all of this in this video, so make sure you do not miss it.
Feel free to write your opinion about this in the comments.
Hope you'll enjoy the video!
 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Transcript:

The 49th parallel was chosen to define most of the border between the United States and Canada. 
And this was not a good idea. You see, using straight lines as borders often leads to situations like these two: US towns completely surrounded by Canada. 
The northernmost town in Minnesota, Angle Inlet, home to just 54 people, is completely cut off from the United States, being surrounded by Canada to the north and 
a lake to the south. The other US town surrounded by Canada is located in Washington state. This is Point Roberts, with a population of 1,200 people. 
What's interesting is that there are no hospitals and schools, and to reach the United States you'll have to cross two checkpoints just to be treated at a hospital in your own country. 
Another cool thing is that in Stanstead, the 49th parallel runs exactly in the middle of this road, and crossing the road can be taken as illegal border crossing.middle of the river in the village called Schengen, which gave the name to the Schengen area.

Importance of Laxmi Mata : 
Goddess Lakshmi is the Hindu goddess of wealth, fortune and prosperity (both material and spiritual). Her name is derived from the Sanskrit word ‚ÄòLakshya‚Äô, which means aim or goal. 
She is the wife and Shakti (energy) of Vishnu, one of the principal deities of Hinduism and the Supreme Being in the Vaishnavism Tradition. Lakshmi is also an important deity in Jainism as well as Buddhism. 

Lakshmi is also called 'Sri' or 'Thirumagal' because she is endowed with six auspicious and divine qualities, or gunas, and is the divine strength of Vishnu. 

In Hindu religion, she was born from the churning of the 'Samudra Manthan' and she chose Vishnu as her eternal consort. When Vishnu descended on the Earth as the avatars Rama and Krishna, Lakshmi descended as his respective consort. The marriage and relationship between Lakshmi and Vishnu as wife and husband is the paradigm for rituals and ceremonies for the bride and groom in Hindu weddings.

Lakshmi is depicted in Indian art as an elegantly dressed, prosperity-showering golden-coloured woman with an owl as her vehicle, signifying the importance of economic activity in the maintenance of life, her ability to move, work and prevail in confusing darkness. 

She is often depicted as part of the Trinity (Tridevi) consisting of Saraswati, Lakshmi and Parvati.
The festivals of Diwali and Sharad Purnima (Kojagiri Purnima) are celebrated in her honour.

Benefits of Performing Maa Lakshmi Aarti :

Lakshmi Aarti is majorly done on Diwali, office/ house-warmings to take the blessings of the goddess of Wealth, Luxury and Prosperity. The Hindu culture strongly believes that Goddess Lakshmi Provides one with financial wellbeing and material gains.

WHAT IS A HOME WARRANTY?
A home warranty is a year-long, renewable home service plan that helps with the cost to repair or replace parts of a home‚Äôs systems and appliances. Home warranties can also be referred to as home warranty policies, home warranty insurance, or home protection plans. It‚Äôs not homeowners insurance, but acts as a complement to it ‚Äì protecting things that your insurance doesn‚Äôt. 

Your home systems and appliances, like your water heater and oven, will break down over time. And sometimes, things just stop working, no matter how old they are. It happens. That‚Äôs where a home warranty comes in ‚Äì offering a budget-friendly solution for covered household breakdowns.

And if it‚Äôs peace of mind and convenience you‚Äôre looking for, we‚Äôve got you covered. Our service plans remove the guesswork. No time spent asking for repair recommendations or calling contractor after contractor. When things go wrong in your home, you‚Äôll know exactly what to do. 

WHAT IS COVERED IN A HOME WARRANTY?
We help protect major parts of your home systems and appliances, no matter their age, no maintenance records or home inspections required. It's similar to appliance insurance or system‚Äôs insurance that you may have for one item, but our home warranties help cover multiple items. Depending on the type of warranty you choose, we cover components of home systems, appliances, or both ‚Äì things like your heating system, water heater, electrical system, dishwasher, clothes washer/dryer, and more.

And if we can‚Äôt repair a covered item, we‚Äôll replace it. As a member, we want you to know that your budget, your time, and, let‚Äôs be honest, your sanity is all good. 

See the plan contract at https://www.ahs.com/contracts/ for coverage details, including service fees, limitations and exclusions. Charges for non-covered items may apply.

Title: Why Electric Cars AREN'T FUN!
Description:
Change your car with Carwow: https://bit.ly/Change-Your-Car-2409 

Can an electric car be fun to drive on track? Well to find out, we've got our hands on one of the most exciting EVs around, the Hyundaio IONIQ 5 N, and we're going to compare it around Silverstone against a BMW M2 Competition!

So let's see how the two compare. Starting with the Hyundai, it‚Äôs powered by two electric motors which combine to produce 650hp and 770Nm of torque. Due to the two motors, it has four-wheel drive, and it weighs in at 2,235kg. As new, an IONIQ 5 N costs around ¬£65,000. 

Then we come to the BMW. It comes with the same 3-litre twin-turbo straight-six as found in the latest M3, but the output has been dialled down slightly, so it‚Äôll produce 460hp and 550Nm of torque. This power is delivered to the rear wheels only, and it tips the scales at 1,725kg. If you‚Äôre looking to buy one new, it‚Äôll set you back around ¬£65,000. 

So do you think the EV sceptic will find any positives when taking the IONIQ on track? You'll need to stick with Mat and Sam to see for yourself!

Title: Why is it called Mercedes?
Description:
Mercedes CEO Ola Kallenius tells why the company is called Mercedes.

The name "Mercedes" comes from a young girl named Mercedes Jellinek, the daughter of Emil Jellinek, a wealthy businessman and automobile enthusiast. In the early 1900s, Jellinek was heavily involved with the German car company Daimler-Motoren-Gesellschaft (DMG), which was producing cars under the Daimler name.

Emil Jellinek was passionate about cars and even raced them, and he ordered a series of vehicles from DMG with custom specifications. He insisted that these cars be marketed under the name "Mercedes," after his daughter, as he believed it would give them a more elegant, exotic, and feminine image that would appeal to wealthy buyers.

The "Mercedes" name became so popular and synonymous with high-performance, luxury vehicles that DMG officially adopted it as their brand name in 1902. Later, the company would merge with Benz & Cie, forming what we now know as Mercedes-Benz.

Disney and Pixar‚Äôs ‚ÄúInside Out 2‚Äù returns to the mind of newly minted teenager Riley just as headquarters is undergoing a sudden demolition to make room for something entirely unexpected: new Emotions! Title: A lente para todas as luzes
Chili Garlic Noodles | Hakka Noodles Recipe | Noodles Recipe | Home Cooking Show
Description:
Chili Garlic Noodles | Hakka Noodles Recipe | Noodles Recipe | Home Cooking Show

Chili Garlic Noodles is a perfect meal with delectable flavours. You can enjoy this with tomato sauce or any side dish of your choice.

#ChiliGarlicNoodles #noodles #noodlerecipe #chilligarlicnoodles #homecookingshow #hakkanoodles #homecooking #hemasubramanian 

Here is the link to Amazon HomeCooking Store where I have curated products that I use and are similar to what I use for your reference and purchase 
https://www.amazon.in/shop/homecookingshow 

Prep Time: 10 mins
Cook Time: 20 mins
Servings: 2 

Ingredients

Hakka Noodles - 300 Gms
Sesame Oil - 2 Tbsp (Buy: https://amzn.to/37oEDA0)
Garlic 
Onion - 1 no. (thinly sliced)
Green Chili - 1 no. (finely chopped)
Carrot - 1 no. (cut into julienne)
Cabbage - 1 bowl (shredded)
Yellow Bell Pepper - 1/2 no. (thinly sliced)
Red Bell Pepper - 1/2 no. (thinly sliced)
Green Capsicum - 1/2 no. (thinly sliced)
Spring Onion Whites 
Vinegar - 2 tsp (Buy: https://amzn.to/38YccsQ)
Soy Sauce - 2 tbsp (Buy: https://amzn.to/2Oq9bKi)
Red Chili Sauce - 1 tbsp (Buy: https://amzn.to/2tdMscS)
Green Chili Sauce - 1 tbsp (Buy: https://amzn.to/2UjQdZt)
Pepper - 1 tsp (Buy: https://amzn.to/2RElrrg)
Spring Onion Greens
Water
Salt (Buy: https://amzn.to/2vg124l)

Method
1. For the noodles to cook ‚Äì take a pan, add enough water, add some salt as required and add Hakka noodles.
2. Once its 90% cooked take it off the flame and strain it, add some oil so that it won't stick to each other.
3. Take a pan, add sesame oil, some finely chopped garlic, onion and green chili.
4. Now start adding vegetables like carrot , shredded cabbage, yellow red and green bell pepper, some spring onion whites. (You can add other vegetables of your choice too)
5. Then add vinegar, soy sauce, red chili sauce, green chili sauce and pepper powder.
6. Finally, add the cooked noodles and toss it all together. Stir fry the noodles for 10 mins.
7. Check for seasoning and add salt if required. 
8. Garnish it with some spring onion greens.
9. Serve the Chili Garlic Noodles hot.

Importance of Laxmi Mata : 
Goddess Lakshmi is the Hindu goddess of wealth, fortune and prosperity (both material and spiritual). Her name is derived from the Sanskrit word ‚ÄòLakshya‚Äô, which means aim or goal. 
She is the wife and Shakti (energy) of Vishnu, one of the principal deities of Hinduism and the Supreme Being in the Vaishnavism Tradition. Lakshmi is also an important deity in Jainism as well as Buddhism. 

Lakshmi is also called 'Sri' or 'Thirumagal' because she is endowed with six auspicious and divine qualities, or gunas, and is the divine strength of Vishnu. 

In Hindu religion, she was born from the churning of the 'Samudra Manthan' and she chose Vishnu as her eternal consort. When Vishnu descended on the Earth as the avatars Rama and Krishna, Lakshmi descended as his respective consort. The marriage and relationship between Lakshmi and Vishnu as wife and husband is the paradigm for rituals and ceremonies for the bride and groom in Hindu weddings.

Lakshmi is depicted in Indian art as an elegantly dressed, prosperity-showering golden-coloured woman with an owl as her vehicle, signifying the importance of economic activity in the maintenance of life, her ability to move, work and prevail in confusing darkness. 

She is often depicted as part of the Trinity (Tridevi) consisting of Saraswati, Lakshmi and Parvati.
The festivals of Diwali and Sharad Purnima (Kojagiri Purnima) are celebrated in her honour.

Benefits of Performing Maa Lakshmi Aarti :

Lakshmi Aarti is majorly done on Diwali, office/ house-warmings to take the blessings of the goddess of Wealth, Luxury and Prosperity. The Hindu culture strongly believes that Goddess Lakshmi Provides one with financial wellbeing and material gains.

Title: All The Hidden Stories in Our Bodies
Description:
The human body is a meticulous record keeper. Every meal, every bout of sickness, every environmental exposure leaves its mark on our tissues

Modern science, through advanced techniques in genetics, biochemistry, and imaging, can read these records, offering insights not just into individual health but also into our ancestral past. One of the most fascinating examples of this is √ñtzi the Iceman, a 5,300-year-old mummy discovered preserved in the Alps.

Analysis of √ñtzi's body has revealed an incredible amount of detail about his life and times. Scientists have determined his age at death, his likely occupation, and even his diet‚Äîhis last meal consisted of wild grains and meat, indicating a balanced use of available resources. Isotopic analysis of his tooth enamel has provided clues about his geographic origin and migrations during his lifetime. Furthermore, the contents of his intestines and the condition of his teeth have told us about the diseases he suffered and his dietary patterns over the years.

The Unexpected Snow Capital of the World
Description:
When we think of snow, countries like Canada, Russia, or Norway typically spring to mind. Yet, the title of the snowiest country on Earth goes to a rather unexpected contender: Japan. 

In the heart of Japan's main island, Honshu, lies the city of Aomori, which on average receives an astounding 311 inches of snow annually. This is more than double the average snowfall in Moscow, Russia, which gets about 152 inches. Even in famously frosty areas like Quebec City in Canada, which sees an average of 124 inches of snow each year, the figures pale in comparison to Japan‚Äôs snowy record.

The Oldest Nation in the World?
Description:
France is often considered the first modern nation in history due to its early development of national identity, centralized government, and defined borders. While other empires and kingdoms existed before, France was one of the first to establish the key elements that would come to define a modern nation-state.

While great civilizations like Rome, Egypt, and China built vast empires, they didn‚Äôt foster the kind of unified national identity or governance we associate with modern nations today. These empires were collections of diverse peoples, often ruled through local authorities and distant, imperial oversight.

Title: Meet Maria (the LA convenience store owner who refuses to sell vapes)
Description:
LOS ANGELES, CA ‚Äî Maria and her husband have owned La Paloma Market for 24 years. Despite being offered ‚Äúa good price‚Äù to stock vapes, they refuse to sell vapes or advertise cigarettes or tobacco products. 

As a mom of a 16-year-old son, Maria says she ‚Äúwouldn't want stores selling vapes and tobacco to my kid, so I‚Äôve never sold them. No profit is worth that ugliness.‚Äù 

A California without Big Tobacco isn‚Äôt just possible. It‚Äôs already happening.
See our progress at UNDO.org.

Consider this 
At La Paloma Market, Maria and her family proudly put people first ‚Äì and they‚Äôre not alone. Consider California‚Äôs Healthy Stores for a Healthy Community program (https://healthystoreshealthycommunity.com/), which aims to improve the health of Californians through changes in community stores and The Stop Tobacco Access to Kids Enforcement (STAKE) Program (https://www.cdph.ca.gov/Programs/CEH/DFDCS/Pages/OfficeofYouthTobaccoEnforcement.aspx), which targets illegal sales of tobacco products to under-21-year-olds.

Title: Visiting the largest Hindu Temple in The USA BAPS Shri Swaminarayan (2nd in the world)
Description:
Welcome to the breathtaking beauty of BAPS Shri Swaminarayan Mandir in Robbinsville, New Jersey! Dive into the mesmerizing world of Indian architecture and spirituality as we take you on a virtual tour of this spiritual marvel.

In this video, I walk through the intricate craftsmanship and detailed carvings that adorn every inch of this sacred sanctuary. Learn about the rich cultural heritage and spiritual significance behind each element of the mandir, from the majestic spires to the tranquil prayer halls that took over 4 million man hours to hand carve.

Join us as I walk through the serene surroundings of the mandir complex, featuring lush gardens, reflective ponds, and peaceful pathways for contemplation and meditation.

Whether you're a seasoned devotee or simply curious about Indian culture and spirituality, this video offers a captivating glimpse into the profound beauty and tranquility of BAPS Shri Swaminarayan Mandir in Robbinsville.

Title: McLaren 750S v Lambo Revuelto: DRAG RACE
Description:

It‚Äôs time for a Britain vs Italy showdown! 

We‚Äôve got Mat in the McLaren 750S, and he‚Äôs going head-to-head against Yianni in his Lamborghini Revuelto! The question is, can the RWD McLaren really take down the 4WD Lambo? Let‚Äôs take a closer look‚Ä¶ 

Starting with the McLaren, it‚Äôs powered by a 4-litre twin-turbo V8 that can produce 750hp and 800Nm of torque. This power is sent to the rear wheels via a 7-speed dual-clutch gearbox, and the car weighs in at 1,389kg. As new, a 750S will set you back around ¬£254,000. 

Then we have the Lambo. It‚Äôs powered by a 6.5-litre naturally-aspirated V12 and three electric motors. Combined they can put down 1,015hp and 1,062Nm, and this power is sent to all four wheels. The car tips the scales at just under 2 tonnes, and as new it‚Äôs a whole lot more expensive than the McLaren, costing around ¬£447,000. 

So the Lambo has the most power, but the McLaren is SO much lighter! Will the weight difference prove decisive? There‚Äôs only one way to find out for sure‚Ä¶ LET‚ÄôS RACE!

Episode 495 :  santosh & karishma funny moment
-----------------------------------------------
In this episode, Karishma tries to trap Chinky and Chintu and pretend to be an Egyptian thief who stole the mummy's coffin. They try to make sure it isn't a scam and video calls them. Pushpaji saves the day and they talk to them with their faces covered. Later, at the exchange of the coffin, Chinty and Chintu manages to escape but get caught by Chandramukhi Chautala.

About The Show:
-----------------------------
Set in Lucknow the show is based in one such all-women Police station made by 4 beautiful quirky women. Pushpa, the oldest of them, is the head constable who tries to balance her life between home and work. Karishma, the Sub Inspector, is fish out of the water as she is at loggerheads with the philosophy of the police station. She beats before she talks but now she has to solve all cases through reconciliation. Santosh Sharma is the young new recruit and a typical lonely girl in the city.
